snippet: The Tokyo String Quartet, which is disbanding, said farewell to its longtime association with the Norfolk Chamber Music Festival with a program of Haydn, Debussy and Bartok.
abstract: Corinna da Fonseca-Wollheim reviews performance by Tokyo String Quartet at the Norfolk Chamber Music Festival in Norfolk, Conn.
lead_paragraph: The Tokyo String Quartet, which is disbanding, said farewell to its longtime association with the Norfolk Chamber Music Festival with a program of Haydn, Debussy and Bartok.

headline.seo: The Tokyo String Quartet Says Farewell at Norfolk Festival
headline.main: A Chamber Ensemble’s Passionate Swan Song
headline.print_headline: A Chamber Ensemble’s Passionate Swan Song
